Defendant Reaquan D Maniece in court with attorney Calvin R. Malone.  Defendant Reaquan D Maniece in custody.  Benjamin Lindsay appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.   

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, Consecutive to any sentence, with credit for 193 days. Huber privileges under Sec. 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work and follow up-care treatment.  No electronic monitoring allowed.  
The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS with the following conditions.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Obtain AODA assessment and complete follow-up care/treatment; 
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No illegal drugs or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*No contact with Mr. DeWitt;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Obtain GED or HSED;
*Cognative thinking evaluation; cooperate with any treatment deemed appropriate by the agent;
*Perform 25 hours of community service during term of probation;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  
*The Court ordered restitution in the amount of $19.00, joint/several payable to John DeWitt.

